<body>
  <h1>Privacy &amp; cookies</h1>
  <p class="lede">What this site collects, what it doesn&rsquo;t, and how to change your mind.</p>

  <div class="pledge">
    <strong>We do not sell your data. Ever.</strong>
    We do not share it with third parties for marketing. There is no ad network on this site.
    The only outbound telemetry is the two analytics tools listed below, used solely to keep the game working and improve it.
  </div>

  <h2>What we collect</h2>
  <p>Three categories, in plain terms:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Authentication cookies (strictly necessary).</strong> Small first-party cookies that prove you&rsquo;re signed in. Without them, the site can&rsquo;t tell you apart from anyone else and you can&rsquo;t play. You cannot disable these and use the site.</li>
    <li><strong>Microsoft Clarity (optional, requires consent).</strong> Anonymous session replay and heatmaps so we can see where players get stuck and fix UX bugs. Loaded only after you click &ldquo;Accept&rdquo; on the cookie banner. We never feed it any account identifier; Clarity also masks input fields by default. After Accept we generate a random per-browser ID stored in <code>localStorage.zd_clarity_id</code> and pass it to Clarity so reloads and tabs in the same browser map to one visitor instead of fragmenting into many &mdash; the ID is not tied to your account and never leaves your browser except as that opaque token.</li>
    <li><strong>Cloudflare Web Analytics (cookieless, always on).</strong> Cloudflare injects a tiny beacon at the network edge to count page views and measure load times. It uses no cookies, no fingerprinting, and no cross-site identifiers, which is why it&rsquo;s exempt from consent requirements under GDPR &amp; ePrivacy. We cannot turn it off from inside the app &mdash; it runs in the proxy layer before your browser ever sees our HTML.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Cookies in use</h2>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Name</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Retention</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>player_session</code></td><td>Keeps you logged in as a player.</td><td>Session / signed out on logout</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>admin_session</code></td><td>Keeps the operator logged in to /admin.</td><td>Session / signed out on logout</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>admin_login_clicks</code></td><td>Counts empty-field clicks for the admin bootstrap interaction.</td><td>Few minutes, deleted automatically</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>admin_bootstrap_ready</code></td><td>Short-lived gate that authorizes the very first admin password to be set.</td><td>Few minutes, deleted automatically</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>admin_variation</code></td><td>Remembers an admin UI preference toggle.</td><td>Until cleared</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>What we do not do</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>We do not sell, rent, or trade your data.</li>
    <li>We do not share data with advertising networks. There are none.</li>
    <li>We do not build profiles of you across other sites.</li>
    <li>We do not run third-party trackers beyond the two analytics tools above.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Your controls</h2>
  <p>You can change your cookie choice at any time. The banner shows on your first visit; once you&rsquo;ve answered, a small &ldquo;Cookies&rdquo; link sits in the bottom-right corner of every page.</p>
  <div class="actions">
    <button type="button" onclick="if(window.__zdConsent && window.__zdConsent.openModal) window.__zdConsent.openModal();">Manage cookies</button>
    <button type="button" onclick="if(window.__zdConsent && window.__zdConsent.reset) window.__zdConsent.reset();">Reset consent</button>
    <a href="/">Back to the lobby</a>
  </div>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>Questions about this page? Reach the operator via the contact channel listed in the project README.</p>
</body>
